File: Authorities are investigating the cause of the blaze. JOHANNESBURG - A community in Ladysmith is in mourning, following the death of a grandmother and her three grandchildren in Ezakheni. The children, an eight-month old baby, and a 7 and a 10-year-old, were asleep when their house caught fire. Authorities are investigating the cause of the blaze. Another relative is still in hospital. The KZN government will be visiting the family on Saturday The family says this a huge loss.